import{_ as e,o,c as t,b as a}from"./app-de7a4551.js";const s={},c=a('<h1 id="computer-knowledge" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#computer-knowledge" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Computer Knowledge</h1><p>Computers have become an <code>integral</code> part of our daily lives. From communication to entertainment, computers have revolutionized the way we live and work. To fully <code>utilize</code> the benefits of computers, it is essential to have a basic understanding of computer knowledge.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>电脑已经成为我们日常生活中不可或缺的一部分。从交流到娱乐，电脑彻底改变了我们生活和工作的方式。为了充分利用电脑的好处，了解基本的计算机知识至关重要。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>integral<br><code>美: [ɪnˈteɡrəl] 英: [ˈɪntɪɡrəl]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 整体；【数】积分<br> adj. 必需的；不可或缺的；作为组成部分的；完整的</p></blockquote><p>utilize<br><code>美: [ˈjut(ə)lˌaɪz] 英: [ˈjuːtɪlaɪz]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 利用；运用；使用；应用</p></blockquote></details><p>Firstly, it is important to understand the hardware components of a computer. This includes the central processing unit (CPU), memory (RAM), hard drive, and graphics card. Knowing how these components work together is <code>crucial</code> for <code>maintaining</code> and upgrading a computer.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>首先，了解计算机硬件组件非常重要。这包括中央处理器(CPU)、内存(RAM)、硬盘和显卡。知道这些组件如何协同工作对于维护和升级计算机至关重要。</p><p>hard drive -&gt; 硬盘驱动器</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>crucial<br><code>美: [ˈkruʃ(ə)l] 英: [ˈkruːʃ(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 至关重要的；关键性的</p></blockquote><p>maintain<br><code>美: [meɪnˈteɪn] 英: [meɪn&#39;teɪn]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 维护；保持；坚持；维持…关系</p></blockquote></details><p>Secondly, understanding computer software is equally important. This includes operating systems such as Windows and macOS, as well as applications like Microsoft Office and Adobe Creative <code>Suite</code>. Learning how to install and use software <code>effectively</code> can save time and improve productivity.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>其次，了解计算机软件同样很重要。这包括诸如Windows和macOS之类的操作系统，以及Microsoft Office和Adobe Creative Suite等应用程序。学习如何有效地安装和使用软件可以节省时间并提高生产力。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>suite<br><code>美: [swit] 英: [swiːt]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 套房；一套家具；组曲（由三个或更多相关部分组成）；套装软件</p></blockquote><p>effectively<br><code>美: [ɪˈfektɪvli] 英: [ɪˈfektɪv(ə)li]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 实际上；有效地；事实上</p></blockquote></details><p>Thirdly, having basic computer skills is essential for everyday tasks such as browsing the internet, sending emails, and using social media. These skills are not only useful for personal use but also for <code>professional</code> purposes in today&#39;s <code>digital</code> age.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>第三，掌握基本的计算机技能对于日常任务非常重要，例如浏览互联网、发送电子邮件和使用社交媒体。这些技能不仅对个人有用，而且在当今数字时代也对职业有用。</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>professional<br><code>美: [prəˈfeʃ(ə)nəl] 英: [prə&#39;feʃ(ə)nəl]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 专家；专业人士；内行；职业运动员<br> adj. 职业的；专业的；有职业的；娴熟的</p></blockquote><p>digital<br><code>美: [ˈdɪdʒɪt(ə)l] 英: [&#39;dɪdʒɪt(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 数字信息系统的；数码的；数字式的；数位的<br> n. 数字电视</p></blockquote></details><p>Lastly, staying up-to-date with technology advancements is crucial for continued success in the field of computer science. Keeping <code>track</code> of new developments in areas such as <code>artificial</code> <code>intelligence</code>, <code>cybersecurity</code>, and cloud computing can help <code>individuals</code> stay competitive in the job market.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>最后，保持对技术发展的更新是计算机科学领域持续成功的关键。追踪人工智能、网络安全和云计算等领域的新发展可以帮助个人在就业市场上保持竞争力。</p><p>up-to-date-&gt; 最新的；现代的；最新式的<br> cybersecurity -&gt; cyber (电脑(网络)的)+ security (安全)</p></details><details class="custom-container details"><summary>words</summary><p>track<br><code>美: [træk] 英: [træk]</code></p><blockquote><p>v. 跟踪；追踪；（尤指用特殊电子设备）跟踪；跟踪（进展情况）<br> n. 轨道；车辙；小径；路线</p></blockquote><p>artificial<br><code>美: [ˌɑrtɪˈfɪʃ(ə)l] 英: [ˌɑː(r)tɪˈfɪʃ(ə)l]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 人工的；人造的；假的；人为的<br> n. 人造肥料；〈美〉假花</p></blockquote><p>intelligence<br><code>美: [ɪnˈtelɪdʒəns] 英: [ɪnˈtelɪdʒ(ə)ns]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 智力；智慧；才智；（尤指关于敌国的）情报</p></blockquote><p>cyber<br><code>美: [&#39;saɪbə] 英: [&#39;saɪbə]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 电脑(网络)的</p></blockquote><p>security<br><code>美: [sɪˈkjʊrəti] 英: [sɪˈkjʊərəti]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 安全；证券；担保；保证</p></blockquote><p>individual<br><code>美: [ˌɪndɪˈvɪdʒuəl] 英: [.ɪndɪ&#39;vɪdʒuəl]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 独立单位；〈俚〉人<br> adj. 单一的；特有的；个体的</p></blockquote></details><p>In conclusion, having a basic understanding of computer knowledge is essential for anyone who wants to make the most out of their computer usage. By learning about hardware components, software applications, everyday tasks, and technology advancements, individuals can improve their productivity and stay ahead in the ever-evolving world of technology.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p>总之，对于想要充分利用计算机的人来说，了解基本的计算机知识是必不可少的。通过学习硬件组件、软件应用程序、日常任务和科技发展，个人可以提高生产力并跟上不断发展的技术世界的步伐。</p><p>ever-evolving -&gt; 时刻演进；不断演进；永远处於发展变化之中的<br> make the most out of -&gt; 充分利用<br> technology advancements -&gt; 科技进步</p></details>',18),i=[c];function n(r,d){return o(),t("div",null,i)}const u=e(s,[["render",n],["__file","01-computer.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
